false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 9, "created_at": "2022-07-10T09:39:30Z", "updated_at": "2023-03-07T05:29:09Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I wrote a function that works with a fairly large array of constants.\r\nOn windows it crashed with \"(exit code: 0xc00000fd, STATUS_STACK_OVERFLOW)\"\r\n\r\nI subsequently minimized my code to the following:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nconst BIG_ARRAY: [usize; 65536] = [0; 65536];\r\n\r\npub fn recursive(depth: usize) -> usize {\r\n    if depth < 3 {\r\n        recursive(depth+1) + recursive(depth+1)\r\n    } else {\r\n        BIG_ARRAY[depth]\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nObviously, this function should not be smashing the stack.\r\n\r\nIn Godbolt I see the following assembly output for my test function\r\n```asm\r\nexample::recursive:\r\n  movl $524344, %eax\r\n  callq __rust_probestack\r\n  subq %rax, %rsp\r\n  ...\r\n```\r\n\r\nRust is allocating space for the entire array of constants on the stack!\r\nI looked at the assembly, and as far as I can tell this space was only allocated but not used.\r\n\r\nThis happens on rust 1.62 as well as on nightly.\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/99111/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/99111/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}